### Named Routes

Named routes provide a simple way to navigate using route names.

```dart
MaterialApp(
  initialRoute: '/',
  routes: {
    '/': (context) => const HomeScreen(),
    '/products': (context) => const ProductsScreen(),
    '/cart': (context) => const CartScreen(),
  },
)

// Usage
Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/products');
Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/cart');
```

### Passing Arguments with Named Routes

```dart
// Push with arguments
Navigator.pushNamed(
  context,
  '/product-detail',
  arguments: Product(id: 1, name: 'Widget'),
);

// Receiving arguments
class ProductDetailScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final product = ModalRoute.of(context)!.settings.arguments as Product;
    return Text(product.name);
  }
}

// Route definition
MaterialApp(
  routes: {
    '/product-detail': (context) => const ProductDetailScreen(),
  },
)
```

### onGenerateRoute

For more control or handling unknown routes:

```dart
MaterialApp(
  initialRoute: '/',
  onGenerateRoute: (settings) {
    // Handle named routes
    if (settings.name == '/profile') {
      final userId = settings.arguments as String;
      return MaterialPageRoute(
        builder: (context) => ProfileScreen(userId: userId),
      );
    }
    // Handle unknown routes
    return MaterialPageRoute(
      builder: (context) => const NotFoundScreen(),
    );
  },
)
```

### Router (Flutter 3.7+)

For complex navigation, use the `Router` API:

```dart
class MyRouterDelegate extends RouterDelegate<String> {
  // Implement custom routing logic
}

MaterialApp.router(
  routerDelegate: MyRouterDelegate(),
  routeInformationParser: MyRouteInformationParser(),
)
```

### Deep Linking

Flutter supports deep linking for web and mobile:

```dart
MaterialApp(
  routes: {
    '/': (context) => const HomeScreen(),
    '/products/:id': (context) => const ProductDetailScreen(),
  },
  // For web deep linking
  usePathUrlStrategy: true,
)
```

| Approach | Complexity | Use Case |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| Basic named routes | Low | Simple apps |
| `onGenerateRoute` | Medium | Dynamic routes |
| Router API | High | Complex navigation |
| go_router package | Medium | Declarative routing |

> **Key Point:** Use named routes for simple apps. Use `onGenerateRoute` when you need to handle arguments or unknown routes. Consider `go_router` package for production apps with complex routing needs.

codeExample:
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() => runApp(const MyApp());

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      initialRoute: '/',
      routes: {
        '/': (context) => const HomeScreen(),
        '/about': (context) => const AboutScreen(),
      },
      onGenerateRoute: (settings) {
        if (settings.name == '/user') {
          final userId = settings.arguments as String;
          return MaterialPageRoute(
            builder: (context) => UserScreen(userId: userId),
          );
        }
        return MaterialPageRoute(
          builder: (context) => const NotFoundScreen(),
        );
      },
    );
  }
}

class HomeScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const HomeScreen({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Home')),
      body: Center(
        child: Column(
          mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
          children: [
            ElevatedButton(
              onPressed: () => Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/about'),
              child: const Text('About'),
            ),
            ElevatedButton(
              onPressed: () => Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/user', arguments: '42'),
              child: const Text('User 42'),
            ),
            ElevatedButton(
              onPressed: () => Navigator.pushNamed(context, '/unknown'),
              child: const Text('Unknown Route'),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

class AboutScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const AboutScreen({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => Scaffold(
    appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('About')),
    body: const Center(child: Text('About Page')),
  );
}

class UserScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  final String userId;
  const UserScreen({super.key, required this.userId});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => Scaffold(
    appBar: AppBar(title: Text('User $userId')),
    body: Center(child: Text('User ID: $userId')),
  );
}

class NotFoundScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const NotFoundScreen({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => Scaffold(
    appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('404')),
    body: const Center(child: Text('Page not found')),
  );
}
